piskorski.util.sorting

Class ExternSorting

  • java.lang.Object
    • piskorski.util.sorting.ExternSorting

  • public class ExternSorting
extends java.lang.Object
    ExternSorting provides methods to sort a file of strings stored in a file using the external sort algorithm with two input tapes and two output tapes. Each line in the input file represents a single string by default. However, the end of the string can be marked via using user-defined end-of-string marker.
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Jakub Piskorski - based on the code by Joerg Steffen, DFKI
